protected_spaces_details.description: Outdoor sports facilities incl school playing fields

description: Demolition of existing buildings to rear and erection of a total of 9 buildings comprising 5 No. 2-4 storey buildings towards the north-eastern boundary, 3 no. 5-7 storey buildings in the central rear portion of the site and one two to two and a half storey buildings towards the rear portion of the south-western boundary.  These buildings to contain 11  three bedroom houses, 3 four bedroom houses, 8 five bedroom houses, 18 one bedroom flats, 77 two bedroom flats and 2 three bedroom flats with associated landscaping, parking, play area and the provision of publicly accessible open land to the rear. 36 of the housing units (blocks D, K and L) would be provided as affordable housing.
decision_conditions: Condition : 1 - The development of large blocks of flats would appear unduly obtrusive and out of scale and character with the surrounding two storey houses. It represents an over intensive development on part of the site, that fails to have adequate regard to the environmental consequences of the increased traffic or the infrastructure of the area. The development does not relate well to the adjacent townscape or make a positive contribution to the overall environmental quality, and is considered to be of an excessive height. This gives rise to significant harm to the amenities of adjoining residents contrary to U.D.P. policies Env 1.1, Env 1.6 and U.D.P. Review Policies Env-B1.1 and Env-B1.3.
